DESCRIPTION:$8.00 - Tickets for the 7 PM screening of SOCIETY 1989 • USA
  • 99 minutes • dir. Brian Yuzna Thursday\, April 16th at The Orbit Ro
 om (107 N College) $8 dollars | 18+ Showtime: 7pm T RAILER Synopsis : Afte
 r producing Re-Animator \, Brian Yuzna turned his hand to directing with S
 OCIETY —one of the ickiest\, most original body horror shockers of all t
 ime. Teenager Bill Whitney has always felt like the odd one out in his wea
 lthy\, upper-class Beverly Hills family. But his sense of alienation takes
  a sinister turn when he hears an audio recording of his sister’s coming
 -out party\, which seems to implicate his family in a bizarre\, ritualisti
 c orgy. Packing stomach-churning grue courtesy Screaming Mad George ( A Ni
 ghtmare on Elm Street 4 ) and thought-provoking social commentary in equal
  measure\, SOCIETY is a biting satire that culminates in the most gag-indu
 cing “climax” in all of horror history. *Cicada Cinema is dedicated to
  curating a wide variety of films while ensuring a safe and inclusive movi
 egoing experience for all. Our mission to program underrepresented films c
 an lead to screening films that may contain uncomfortable or otherwise ins
 ensitive imagery and content. We encourage you to research the films we pr
 ogram beforehand to determine if they could be upsetting to you. Please fe
 el free to contact us for guidance on any film you may have questions abou
